{"name": "Mary Eliza Mahoney Health Center", "alternate_name": "", "description": "CCC Free Fresh Produce Market for Seniors and Families (Food as Medicine) event happening on Tuesday, March 25.
This special event is presented in partnership with the Rutgers SAVE Cancer Screening Program, Newark Department of Health and Community Wellness, University Hospital, and Horizon Blue Cross and Blue Shield of NJ.
In addition to the free fresh produce market, eligible women will have the opportunity to pre-register for a free breast screening (mammogram) More information on site.
Breast Screening Eligibility: Women age 40 and older Never had a mammogram OR last mammogram was 12+ months ago
Available for both insured and uninsured individuals
Participants can also enter to win great prizes and enjoy shopping at the free fresh produce market!", "email": "", "url": null, "status": "active", "address": {"address_1": "394 University Avenue", "address_2": null, "city": "Central Ward", "state_province": "NJ", "postal_code": "07102", "country": "US"}, "location": {"latitude": 40.7340491, "longitude": -74.17734709999999}, "service_attributes": [{"attribute_key": "INFO", "attribute_value": "Healthcare Programs"}, {"attribute_key": "OFFERING", "attribute_value": "Fresh produce"}]}
